Every second of every day, blood transfusion is critically needed to save a life. Blood and its components are required for survival in emergencies, surgeries, haematological malignancies, pregnancy related complications, in certain diseases like thalassemia and severe anaemia.The only way to get blood is through human blood donation and the most crucial step towards acquiring safe blood and an adequate reserve is to promote a positive disposition towards regular voluntary, non-profit blood donation.The need for blood is a reality shared globally and blood donors are on a steady decline. According to World Health Organization, to meet the requirements for blood in developing countries, 1% of the population needs to donate blood. Please click the link below for voluntary donation in Lagos (LUTH). https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdFUjxL2tZieG7emEn-H5rDz8EtmETlsu6fM_njgUW7L1lnjw/viewform -Advertisement- 